This article summarizes remarks made by President Trump and President Erdoğan of Turkey during a meeting at the Lotte New York Palace Hotel in New York. President Trump introduced President Erdoğan and praised him for his work in a difficult part of the world. The two leaders discussed their strong friendship and the close relationship between the United States and Turkey. They also mentioned that they would be conducting a bilateral meeting to assess the current relations between the two countries and discuss recent regional developments. When asked about the violence against peaceful protestors and the Kurdish issue, President Trump stated that they would be discussing many issues.